05/03/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The chief of the European Commission's delegation to Romania, Jonathan Scheele, said Thursday (4 March) that the EU is fully committed to the country's accession.
Scheele, who participated in a debate organised by the Bucharest-based group European Movement, expressed optimism that Romania would become a member in 2007.
At the same time, he stressed the need for reforms, especially in public administration and the judiciary.
In other news, President Ion Iliescu has signed the promulgation decree for the law on NATO accession.
Parliament passed the law last week.
(Rompres, ACT Media - 05/03/04;
Mediafax, BBC - 04/03/04)
